1 Connection Header Handling (source/common/http/utility.cc)**\n- `sanitizeConnectionHeader()`: Prevents header injection via the Connection header by:\n  - Limiting nominated headers to 10 maximum (prevents DOS)\n  - Removing headers nominated by the Connection header\n  - Rejecting if Connection nominates x-forwarded-* headers or pseudo-headers (RFC violation)\n  - Sanitizing the TE (Transfer-Encoding) header when nominated\n  - Validating TE values do not exceed 256 bytes\n  - Validates nominated headers conform to HTTP hop-by-hop semantics\n\n### HTTP/1.1 Specific Validation\n\n**Header Codec Validation (source/common/http/http1/codec_impl.cc)**\n- Validates header values for invalid characters using `headerValueIsValid()`\n- Checks header names and values conform to HTTP/1.1 semantics\n- Validates path formatting and rejects invalid URLs\n- Calls `sanitizeConnectionHeader()` during request header processing\n- Detects invalid header values (non-ASCII, control characters)\n\n**HTTP/1 Header Validator (source/extensions/http/header_validators/envoy_default/http1_header_validator.cc)**\n- `sanitizeContentLength()`: Removes content-length from CONNECT requests or when transfer-encoding:chunked is present\n- `sanitizeHeadersWithUnderscores()`: Removes or rejects headers with underscores based on configuration\n- `sanitizePathWithFragment()`: Strips URL fragments from paths\n- `transformRequestHeaders()`: Applies all sanitization transformations in sequence\n- Validates header character sets conform to RFC specifications\n- Supports path normalization with escaped slash handling\n\n### HTTP/2 Specific Validation  \n\n**HTTP/2 Forbidden Headers (source/extensions/http/header_validators/envoy_default/http2_header_validator.cc)**\n- Enforces strict validation that connection-specific headers are forbidden in HTTP/2 per RFC 9113\n- Forbidden header list: transfer-encoding, connection, upgrade, keep-alive, proxy-connection\n- Returns ConnectionHeaderSanitization rejection